cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SD 

The paper presents an approach based on spectral graph theory for option discovery in reinforcement learning without access to a specific reward or task assignment. This involves using geometric and manifold-based analysis to justify the algorithm and showcase its performance in several domains. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves graph theory and analysis, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SD (Systems and Control).
